    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1269516736" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1269516736" />
    <a title="Cynda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24011982-cynda"><img alt="Cynda" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1606460118p2/24011982.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1269516736?book_show_action=true">May 01, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cynda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cynda" href="/user/show/24011982-cynda">Cynda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781594482694" href="/book/show/1022807.The_Ghost_Map">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24011982-cynda?shelf=read2017">read2017</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24011982-cynda?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24011982-cynda?shelf=cities">cities</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/24011982-cynda?shelf=medical-science">medical-science</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1269516736" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11859850290945606817">In the <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36086.The_Ghost_Map_The_Story_of_London_s_Most_Terrifying_Epidemic___and_How_It_Changed_Science__Cities__and_the_Modern_World' title='The Ghost Map The Story of London&apos;s Most Terrifying Epidemic - and How It Changed Science, Cities, and the Modern World by Steven Johnson' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Ghost Map: The Story of London&apos;s Most Terrifying Epidemic - and How It Changed Science, Cities, and the Modern World</a>, Johnson has written a history with a number of check marks.<br/><br/>Accessibility? Check<br/>Complete Story? Check.<br/>Argument Well Presented? Check.<br/>Present New Insight? Check.<br/>Present Significance to Us/Contemporaries. Big Check.<br/>Primary Sources? Check. Johnson used committee reports generated in 1850s, various writings of Dr John Snow who realized the water coming from the Broad Street</span>
  <span id="freeText11859850290945606817" style="display:none">In the <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36086.The_Ghost_Map_The_Story_of_London_s_Most_Terrifying_Epidemic___and_How_It_Changed_Science__Cities__and_the_Modern_World" title="The Ghost Map The Story of London's Most Terrifying Epidemic - and How It Changed Science, Cities, and the Modern World by Steven Johnson" rel="nofollow noopener">The Ghost Map: The Story of London's Most Terrifying Epidemic - and How It Changed Science, Cities, and the Modern World</a>, Johnson has written a history with a number of check marks.<br /><br />Accessibility? Check<br />Complete Story? Check.<br />Argument Well Presented? Check.<br />Present New Insight? Check.<br />Present Significance to Us/Contemporaries. Big Check.<br />Primary Sources? Check. Johnson used committee reports generated in 1850s, various writings of Dr John Snow who realized the water coming from the Broad Street pump was the source of cholera-riddled water. Johnson also used a report prepared by Dr Snow's nemesis Mr Edwin Chadwick, a social reformer who insisted it was a miasma, a bad smell.<br />What I would have liked to have seen: The Voronoi diagram that Dr Snow presented to the Cholera Inquiry Committee visually showing where Londoners of Soho got their water. People chose which local water pump to use based on how easy it was to get to, not on how close it was by map measurements. I had to look up it up online. The map on The cover of the edition I am reading is not a Voronoi diagram. The map shown throughout the book does not give the big picture while the image online does. <br />Necessary Point: Steven Johnson is not a historian. He is a popular science writer. He has merged history and popular science to create a book that describes London's Cholera Outbreak in a medical-social context and tells his readers how Londoners now have a plumbing system that takes the waste products away. Other cities now and other cities may need a similar solution to a common problem in burgeoning cities. He also speaks of alternative solutions working in parts of the world, options to a plumbing system. Johnson makes clear that cities are great places for job, cultural development, social interactions and more, so the answer to burgeoning cities is not to disband. It is to cope with the problem.<br />Worthwhile read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11859850290945606817" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


